<div id="t4-main-body" class="t4-section  t4-main-body  container"><div class="t4-section-inner container-fluid"><div class="t4-row row"><div class="t4-col component col-12 col-md-6 col-lg container"><div id="system-message-container" aria-live="polite"></div><div class="com-content-article item-page" ><div class="page-header"><h1 > Financial Annual Return for BVI companies: A complete guide </h1></div><div class="ja-share-button" layout="default" ></div><dl class="article-info text-muted"> <dt class="article-info-term"> Details </dt><dd class="createdby" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"> Written by: <a href="../../../our-experts/author/daniel.html" >Daniel</a> </dd> <span style="display: none;" itemprop="publisher" itemscope> <span >Daniel</span> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject"> <img src="../../../../templates/ja_alpha/images/logo.png" alt="logo" width="160" height="40"> <meta itemprop="width" content="auto" /><meta itemprop="height" content="auto" /></span> </span> <dd class="modified"> <span class="fa fa-calendar" aria-hidden="true"></span> <time datetime="2024-07-15T10:35:06+07:00" itemprop="dateModified"> Last Updated: 15 July 2024	</time> </dd> </dl><ul class="fields-container"> <li class="field-entry country "> <span class="field-label ">Country: </span> <span class="field-value ">BVI</span> </li> <li class="field-entry services "> <span class="field-label ">Services: </span> <span class="field-value ">Tax - Accounting</span> </li> <li class="field-entry rating-count "> <span class="field-label ">Rating Count: </span> <span class="field-value ">17</span> </li> <li class="field-entry rating-value "> <span class="field-label ">Rating Value: </span> <span class="field-value ">5</span> </li></ul><div class="com-content-article__body"><p>Maintaining detailed records and documents has been a standing obligation for BVI companies, ensuring transactions are traceable and the financial status is accurately reflected at any given moment.</p><p>However, under the BVI Business Companies Act amendments 2022, BVI companies are now mandated to annually submit specified financial details to their registered agent via a Financial Annual Return (except in a few cases).</p><p>For this reason, our guide helps you navigate BVI's new financial reporting requirements, ensuring your business adheres to local laws and thrives in a competitive economic environment.Â </p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="financial-annual-return-all-you-need-to-know-first" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.</span> <span class="heading_text">Financial annual return: All you need to know first</span></h2><h3 class="indexed"><span id="what-is-a-bvi-financial-annual-return" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.1.</span> <span class="heading_text">What is a BVI financial annual return?</span></h3><p>BVI financial annual return, also known as a financial return or annual return, consists of a simple income statement (profit and loss statement) and a balance sheet.</p><p>It provides corporate directors and shareholders a lucid understanding of the BVI-registered companyâ€™s financial health and helps ensure your business meets BVI legal demands.</p><p>Highlights of the return's format include:</p><ul> <li>This financial information is to remain confidential, and not intended for public access;</li> <li>Preparing the financial annual return for BVI companies does not require any specific accounting standards. You can use the International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS);</li> <li>The Annual Financial Return does not need to be audited;</li> <li>You need to submit the annual return to your Registered Agent;</li> <li>The form of the return is straightforward. You can see a copy of the Return <a href="https://www.bvifsc.vg/sites/default/files/bvi_business_companies_financial_return_order_2023.pdf" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">here</a>.Â </li> </ul><h3 class="indexed"><span id="what-information-do-bvi-companies-need-to-prepare-for-the-annual-return-filing" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.2.</span> <span class="heading_text">What information do BVI companies need to prepare for the annual return filing?</span></h3><p>To comply with BVI regulations when submitting annual returns, businesses registering a BVI company must gather and prepare the following financial information:</p><p><strong>Balance Sheet components</strong></p><ol> <li><strong>Assets</strong>: A list of everything the company owns, which provides value (e.g., cash, equipment, property).</li> <li><strong>Liabilities</strong>: All debts or obligations the company is responsible for (e.g., loans, payables).</li> <li><strong>Shareholder equity</strong>: The residual interest in assets after deducting liabilities, also known as 'net assets'.</li> </ol><p><strong>Income Statement components</strong></p><ol> <li><strong>Revenue</strong>: The total income generated from the sale of goods or services, before any costs or expenses are deducted.</li> <li><strong>Cost of sales</strong>: The direct costs attributable to the production of the goods sold by the company.</li> <li><strong>Gross profit</strong>: The profit a company makes after deducting the costs associated with making and selling its products or the costs associated with providing its services.</li> <li><strong>Other costs</strong>: This includes operating costs, such as payroll and rent, and corporate income tax, among other expenses.</li> <li><strong>Total expenses</strong>: The sum of all costs and expenses associated with the companyâ€™s operations.</li> <li><strong>Net income (Profit)</strong>: Often referred to as the 'bottom line,' this is the total revenue minus the total expenses.</li> </ol><p>Your company needs to compile these financial details with care to ensure accuracy and adherence to the stipulated BVI reporting standards.</p><h3 class="indexed"><span id="why-do-bvi-companies-need-to-prepare-a-financial-annual-return" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.3.</span> <span class="heading_text">Why do BVI companies need to prepare a financial annual return?</span></h3><p><a href="https://www.oecd.org/tax/transparency/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Global Forum on Transparency and Exchange of Information for Tax Purposes of OECD</a> requires that jurisdictions safeguard the integrity of accounting records across all entities and arrangements.Â </p><p>To conform to these international standards, Â the British Virgin Islands has made drastic changes to the BVI Business Companies Act, thus the need for a financial return. The BVI Financial Services Commission implements this measure to ensure timely access to crucial financial information for international cooperation.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="when-do-bvi-companies-need-to-file-the-bvi-annual-return" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">2.</span> <span class="heading_text">When do BVI companies need to file the BVI annual return?</span></h2><p>In line with revisions to the BVI Business Companies Act, BVI businesses need to present the annual financial return to their Registered Agent <strong>no later than nine months following their financial year-end.</strong></p><p>For example, if a companyâ€™s financial year-end is March 31, 2024,</p><ul> <li>Â It is eligible to start filing the annual return from April 1, 2024.</li> <li>The final date for filing for such a company would be 9 months after the end of their fiscal year, which, in this example, means they have until December 31, 2024, to file their BVI annual return.</li> </ul><h2 class="indexed"><span id="which-type-of-bvi-companies-can-be-exempt-from-the-financial-annual-return-order" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">3.</span> <span class="heading_text">Which type of BVI companies can be exempt from the financial annual return order?</span></h2><p>Under section 98A(5) of the BVI Business Companies Act, certain companies are exempt from the obligation to file an annual return, which includes:</p><table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100.004%; height: 207.955px;" border="1"> <thead> <tr style="height: 20.7955px;"> <td style="width: 5.50703%; height: 20.7955px;">Â </td> <td style="width: 24.4718%; height: 20.7955px;">Types of companies</td> <td style="width: 69.9833%; height: 20.7955px;">Description</td> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr style="height: 41.5909px;"> <td style="width: 5.50703%; height: 41.5909px;">1</td> <td style="width: 24.4718%; height: 41.5909px;">Listed companies</td> <td style="width: 69.9833%; height: 41.5909px;">A company whose shares are traded on a recognized stock exchange is exempt from filing an annual return.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 62.3864px;"> <td style="width: 5.50703%; height: 62.3864px;">2</td> <td style="width: 24.4718%; height: 62.3864px;">Regulated financial services companies</td> <td style="width: 69.9833%; height: 62.3864px;">A company that falls under the purview of financial services legislation and is compliant with the regulatory framework, particularly where it is required to and does submit financial statements directly to the BVI Financial Services Commission.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 62.3864px;"> <td style="width: 5.50703%; height: 62.3864px;">3</td> <td style="width: 24.4718%; height: 62.3864px;">Companies filing annual tax returns with financial statements</td> <td style="width: 69.9833%; height: 62.3864px;">A company that files its annual tax returns with the BVI Inland Revenue Department and includes its audited financial statements as part of that submission.</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 20.7955px;"> <td style="width: 5.50703%; height: 20.7955px;">4</td> <td style="width: 24.4718%; height: 20.7955px;">Companies in liquidation</td> <td style="width: 69.9833%; height: 20.7955px;">A company that is in the process of liquidation is exempt, provided that the requirement to file an Annual Return does not arise before the commencement of the liquidation proceedings.</td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p>Â </p><p>Companies within these classifications need to understand their exemption status to ensure compliance with BVI regulatory requirements.Â </p><p>BVI companies should consult with their Registered Agent or professional consultant to confirm whether they qualify for an exemption, and to understand any obligations that may still apply to them despite the exemption from filing an annual return.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="how-can-we-help-you-prepare-for-the-bvi-financial-annual-return" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">4.</span> <span class="heading_text">How can we help you prepare for the BVI financial annual return?</span></h2><p>Global Link Asia Consulting, as your trusted one-stop corporate service provider helping hundreds of business owners start their businesses overseas and manage their companies with success, can help you</p><ul> <li>Collect data and accounting documents and store them securely via QuickBooks;Â </li> <li>Prepare financial annual return following the International Financial Report Standard;</li> <li>Review collaboratively with company directors for accuracy, prompt submission to avert penalties, and audit support when required.</li> </ul><p>In addition, we can help you:</p><ul> <li><a href="../../../company-incorporation/bvi.html">Register an offshore company in BVI</a>;</li> <li><a href="../../../open-a-bank-account/bank-account-opening-in-offshore.html">Open a corporate bank account for BVI company with a 99% success rate</a>;</li> <li>Choose the right company types for tax optimization;</li> <li>Apply for BVI business licenses;</li> <li>Get an affordable, professional registered office address for business;</li> <li>Support to open, authenticate, and manage Stripe Paypal Business in Singapore, Hong Kong, and the U.S;</li> <li><a href="../../../tax-accounting/tax-accounting-in-offshore.html">Handle all your tax accounting needs, timely annual filings, auditing, and more</a>.</li> </ul><h2 class="indexed"><span id="faqs-about-bvi-s-financial-annual-return" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">5.</span> <span class="heading_text">FAQs about BVIâ€™s financial annual return</span></h2><div data-rlta-element="container" data-rlta-state="initial" data-rlta-id="1" data-rlta-type="accordions" data-rlta-title-tag="div" data-rlta-orientation="vertical" data-rlta-wrap-buttons="false" data-rlta-remember-active="false" data-rlta-theme="neutral" data-rlta-color-panels="false" data-rlta-positioning="top" data-rlta-alignment="left" data-rlta-has-button-scroller="false"><div id="rlta-1-are-there-any-penalties-for-not-meeting-the-bvi-annual-return-filing-requirement" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-1-are-there-any-penalties-for-not-meeting-the-bvi-annual-return-filing-requirement" aria-expanded="true" tabindex="0" class="icon-faq" data-rlta-alias="1-are-there-any-penalties-for-not-meeting-the-bvi-annual-return-filing-requirement" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="open"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 1. Are there any penalties for not meeting the BVI annual return filing requirement?</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-1-are-there-any-penalties-for-not-meeting-the-bvi-annual-return-filing-requirement" aria-labelledby="rlta-1-are-there-any-penalties-for-not-meeting-the-bvi-annual-return-filing-requirement" tabindex="-1" class="icon-faq" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="open" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>Under the recent amendment of the BVI Companies Act, Registered Agents are mandated to report any non-compliance to the BVI Financial Services Commission within one month past the annual return filing deadline.Â </p><p>Non-filing constitutes an offense and could lead to fines, impact the company's good standing, and risk the company being struck off the registrar's list.</p></div></div><div id="rlta-2-which-currency-can-bvi-companies-use-to-prepare-the-bvi-financial-return" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-2-which-currency-can-bvi-companies-use-to-prepare-the-bvi-financial-return" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" class="icon-faq" data-rlta-alias="2-which-currency-can-bvi-companies-use-to-prepare-the-bvi-financial-return" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="closed"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 2. Which currency can BVI companies use to prepare the BVI financial return?</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-2-which-currency-can-bvi-companies-use-to-prepare-the-bvi-financial-return" aria-labelledby="rlta-2-which-currency-can-bvi-companies-use-to-prepare-the-bvi-financial-return" tabindex="-1" class="icon-faq" hidden="true" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="closed" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>A company has the flexibility to prepare its financial statements in any currency. The USD$ notation included in the Annual Return Template serves as a reference and may be replaced with the currency of the company's choice.</p></div></div><div id="rlta-3-does-the-annual-return-need-to-be-audited" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-3-does-the-annual-return-need-to-be-audited" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" class="icon-faq" data-rlta-alias="3-does-the-annual-return-need-to-be-audited" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="closed"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 3. Does the annual return need to be audited?</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-3-does-the-annual-return-need-to-be-audited" aria-labelledby="rlta-3-does-the-annual-return-need-to-be-audited" tabindex="-1" class="icon-faq" hidden="true" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="closed" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>There is no mention in the BVI Business Companies Act 2022 Amendment, along with the Financial Return Order, that the annual returns undergo an audit.</p></div></div><div id="rlta-4-does-the-bvi-annual-return-need-to-follow-any-specific-accounting-standard" role="button" aria-controls="rlta-panel-4-does-the-bvi-annual-return-need-to-follow-any-specific-accounting-standard" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" class="icon-faq" data-rlta-alias="4-does-the-bvi-annual-return-need-to-follow-any-specific-accounting-standard" data-rlta-element="button" data-rlta-state="closed"><div data-rlta-element="heading"> 4. Does the BVI annual return need to follow any specific accounting standard?</div></div><div id="rlta-panel-4-does-the-bvi-annual-return-need-to-follow-any-specific-accounting-standard" aria-labelledby="rlta-4-does-the-bvi-annual-return-need-to-follow-any-specific-accounting-standard" tabindex="-1" class="icon-faq" hidden="true" data-rlta-element="panel" data-rlta-state="closed" data-rlta-color="false"><div data-rlta-element="panel-content"><p>The BVI Business Companies Act does not mandate specific accounting standards, for the preparation of our accounting records and annual returns. That is why, you can use IFRS for BVI Â financial return preparation.</p></div></div></div><p><div id="mod-custom1265" class="mod-custom custom"><div class='jpb-page'><div id="ifrsdm" class="t4b-box glac-box-expand glac-box-collapsed"><p id="i1mya"> We offer a comprehensive range of accounting and tax services for offshore companies. Our services include: </p><div><ul id="iubi7" class="fa-ul"><li id="iro6g"><span id="ixg85" class="fa-li"><i class="fa-solid fa-angle-right"> </i></span><span id="imxvg">Monthly/Annual Tax Accounting services for offshore companies.</span></li><li id="ihd8k"><span class="fa-li"><i id="i6whf" class="fa-solid fa-angle-right"> </i></span><span id="iyx5n">QuickBooks Consulting and Licensing.</span></li><li id="inxip"><span class="fa-li"><i id="iddxg" class="fa-solid fa-angle-right"> </i></span><span id="igfrk">Annual Return Preparation.</span></li><li id="izj4k"><span class="fa-li"><i id="i3gk7" class="fa-solid fa-angle-right"> </i></span><span id="ico2g">Economic Subs